   <abstract lang="eng">In this report a National Aircraft Facility Survey Group was appointed in July 1963. The group was requested to study and report upon requirements for research aircraft and aircraft services (such as instrumentation and data-handling systems) now existing in the scientific community. After five months of study, the group strongly recommended the establishment of a scientific aviation facility at NCAR.</abstract>
